routeFacts.name: Bakerloo Line
routeFacts.description: The Bakerloo line is a London Underground line featured in the base game of Train Sim World 2. The line runs for 14 miles from Harrow & Wealdstone to Elephant & Castle, and runs partially above ground and below ground. The 1972 Mark 2 Stock is featured to run services along the route. The Watford DC line is featured between Harrow & Wealdstone and Queen's Park. Part of the West Coast Main Line is shown running parallel to the Bakerloo line between Queen's Park and Harrow & Wealdstone. There are 25 stations on the Bakerloo line. The Bakerloo line is the first Train Sim World route to feature working Passenger Information Displays.
routeInfo:
Opened between 1906 and 1914, originally known as the Baker Street & Waterloo Railway, it was swiftly renamed to the Bakerloo Line as the public abbreviation of the name had gained popularity. The Bakerloo Line is one of the world's busiest commuter railways and the popularity of the line is less today than it was when it first opened, carrying millions of passengers every year.
The Bakerloo Line is 14.4 miles long and features 25 unique stations, from Elephant & Castle in South London to Harrow & Wealdstone in the North West of the city. It covers many of London's iconic landmarks and famous streets such as Waterloo, Piccadilly Circus, Baker Street and more. There are 10 above-ground and 15 underground stations to discover and the various Timetabled Services and Scenarios in Train Sim World 2 will take you on a tour of these as you explore the full line.
